00:04:44,075 --> 00:04:47,096
你们在找...这个吧?
You'all looking for something like... this?

64
00:04:47,097 --> 00:04:51,001
酷 一个球
Cool, a ball.

65
00:04:51,002 --> 00:04:53,049
我们要来个小小的交易
We need to do a little quid pro quo first.

66
00:04:53,050 --> 00:04:54,082
我离开这里有段时间了
I know I've been gone a while

67
00:04:54,083 --> 00:04:56,010
你们就认为可以把我的东西
and you'all thought the general store

68
00:04:56,011 --> 00:04:58,057
拿到百货商场廉价出售
was having a going out of business sale

69
00:04:58,058 --> 00:05:01,032
但我回来了 我想要回我的东西
but now I'm back, and I want what's mine.

70
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:04,000
但那些东西原本也不是你的
Yeah, but it wasn't really yours to begin with.

71
00:05:04,001 --> 00:05:06,005
"A"-- 那些是我找到的
"A"-- It was mine when I took it.

72
00:05:06,006 --> 00:05:08,090
"B"-- 你又是谁?
"B"-- Who the hell are you?

73
00:05:08,091 --> 00:05:14,056
"C"-- 我很公平 我们用比赛决定
And "C"-- Because I'm fair, I'm gonna let you play me for it.

74
00:05:14,057 --> 00:05:16,039
打乒乓球?
Play ping-Pong?

75
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:18,046
是啊 大块头
That's right, Avalanche.

76
00:05:18,047 --> 00:05:20,025
你们这群家伙尽管挑个打得最好的
You bastards put up your best player.

77
00:05:20,026 --> 00:05:23,058
就一场比赛 我赢了之后
One game, and when I crush them

78
00:05:23,059 --> 00:05:27,003
你们要把我的每样东西都还给我
you'all gotta bring me every piece of my stash back.

79
00:05:27,004 --> 00:05:29,055
如果你输了呢?
And if you lose?

80
00:05:29,056 --> 00:05:32,099
我不会输的 但...
I ain't gonna lose, but..

81
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:41,033
如果我输了...随你们怎么样
if I do, tell you what...name it.

82
00:05:45,077 --> 00:05:51,039
看来"卧虎藏龙"有好的主意
Looks like Crouching Tiger and Hidden Dragon got something good.

83
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:54,035
说吧
Lay it on me.

84
00:05:54,036 --> 00:05:56,045
不许再叫我们的绰号
No nicknames.

85
00:05:56,046 --> 00:06:00,031
如果你输了 一个星期内...
If you lose, no nicknames for anyone...

86
00:06:00,032 --> 00:06:02,070
不许叫我们的绰号
for a week.

87
00:06:02,071 --> 00:06:06,029
好棒
Nice.

88
00:06:06,030 --> 00:06:09,091
成交
You're on.

89
00:06:09,092 --> 00:06:11,013
选出你们的选手吧
Pick your player.

90
00:06:11,014 --> 00:06:17,090
一小时后我会回来 然后我会宰了你们
I'll be back in an hour, then let the slaughter begin.

91
00:06:20,011 --> 00:06:23,079
你确定这房子周围什么都没有？
Are you sure it's completely isolated?

92
00:06:23,080 --> 00:06:25,062
我搜索过周边地带
I've circled the house.

93
00:06:25,063 --> 00:06:28,001
附近除了丛林什么都没有
There's nothing but jungle surrounding it.

94
00:06:28,002 --> 00:06:32,058
给你
Here.

95
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:34,027
那个雷达还能工作吗?
That dish still work?

96
00:06:34,028 --> 00:06:35,070
这样的卫星雷达
A satellite dish of that size would have

97
00:06:35,071 --> 00:06:40,004
能传播几千英里的信息
broadcasting capabilities for thousands of miles.

98
00:06:40,005 --> 00:06:43,056
Danielle 你提到过雷达站
Danielle, you once mentioned a radio tower.

99
00:06:43,057 --> 00:06:45,010
是这个吗?
Is this it?

100
00:06:45,011 --> 00:06:48,057
我从来没有来过这里
I have never been here before.

101
00:06:48,058 --> 00:06:51,002
那里面的男人...你说你见过他?
The man in the house...you said you've seen him before?

102
00:06:51,003 --> 00:06:53,087
就是珍珠站录像里的那个人
On a video feed from the pearl station.

103
00:06:53,088 --> 00:06:55,013
那他是谁?
So who is he?

104
00:06:55,014 --> 00:07:00,020
只有一种办法能找到答案...
Only one way to find out...

105
00:07:00,021 --> 00:07:02,065
我们去问他
we ask him.

106
00:07:02,066 --> 00:07:03,040
这是干嘛?
What's this for?

107
00:07:03,041 --> 00:07:07,000
如果我不带武器 他就不会感到有威胁
If I'm unarmed, he won't feel threatened.

108
00:07:07,001 --> 00:07:11,045
如果他有所动作 你从这里掩护我
In case he is threatened, you can cover me from here.

109
00:07:11,046 --> 00:07:13,008
你去哪儿?
Where are you going?

110
00:07:13,009 --> 00:07:16,035
我对那房子里的男人没兴趣
I have no interest in that man inside the house.

111
00:07:16,036 --> 00:07:23,012
我能生存下来是因为我尽量避免与他们正面接触
I have survived on the island precisely by avoiding these types of encounters.

112
00:07:23,013 --> 00:07:25,067
我会在小溪边等你们...
I'll wait for you by the stream...

113
00:07:25,068 --> 00:07:31,001
等能活下来的
for those of you who survive.

114
00:07:51,037 --> 00:07:55,004
Najeev Najeev

115
00:07:55,005 --> 00:08:00,048
有个人想要见你

116
00:08:09,007 --> 00:08:11,009
这是你做的吗?
Did you cook this?

117
00:08:11,010 --> 00:08:12,073
是的
Yes, I did.

118
00:08:12,074 --> 00:08:16,079
这很美味
It's delicious.

119
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:18,080
我叫Sami
My name is Sami.

120
00:08:18,081 --> 00:08:20,084
Najeev 谢谢你
Najeev. Thank you.

121
00:08:20,085 --> 00:08:25,066
请坐
Please sit.

122
00:08:25,067 --> 00:08:27,031
你从哪里来 Najeev?
So where are you from, Najeev?

123
00:08:27,032 --> 00:08:29,003
我是Syrian人
I'm Syrian.

124
00:08:29,004 --> 00:08:30,017
拜托
Please.

125
00:08:30,018 --> 00:08:37,092
你和我一样是伊拉克人吧 年轻人

126
00:08:40,077 --> 00:08:42,071
你想怎么样?
What do you want from me?

127
00:08:42,072 --> 00:08:46,090
你是个出色的厨师 我...
You're an excellent cook, and I...

128
00:08:46,091 --> 00:08:50,070
有一个很好的餐馆
I have a restaurant much nicer than this place.

129
00:08:50,071 --> 00:08:52,080
来看看吧
Come take a look.

130
00:08:52,081 --> 00:08:58,009
如果你喜欢 我会付你双倍的工资
If you like it, I will hire you at twice your pay here.

131
00:08:58,010 --> 00:09:01,027
就凭一顿饭你就会雇佣一个陌生人?
You're offering a stranger a job because of a single meal?

132
00:09:01,028 --> 00:09:05,083
我给你工作是因为我和你都是外来者
I'm offering you a job because we are outsiders here

133
00:09:05,084 --> 00:09:13,011
我的主厨刚好辞职了
and because, uh, my chef just quit.

134
00:09:52,037 --> 00:09:54,004
他中弹了
He's been hit, he's been hit!

135
00:09:54,069 --> 00:09:55,045
你也想被射到吗?
You wanna get shot, too?

136
00:09:55,046 --> 00:09:57,006
我没有越线!
I didn't cross the line!

137
00:09:57,007 --> 00:09:58,038
我们有停战协议的
We had a truce.

138
00:09:58,039 --> 00:09:59,009
这是我的地盘!
This is my land!

139
00:09:59,010 --> 00:10:00,084
我不是...你们说我可以待在这里的!
I'm not.. You said I could stay here!

140
00:10:00,085 --> 00:10:03,058
我不是..你说的那个人
I'm not who you..Who you think I am.

141
00:10:03,059 --> 00:10:05,082
我叫Sayid Jarrah
My name is Sayid Jarrah.

142
00:10:05,083 --> 00:10:10,059
几个月前我们的飞机坠毁了
I was on a plane that crashed here months ago.

143
00:10:10,060 --> 00:10:12,010
飞机?!
A plane?!

144
00:10:12,011 --> 00:10:17,032
我发誓我没有武器!
I'm unarmed, I swear!

145
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:22,061
待在那儿别动!
Stay right there!

146
00:10:31,018 --> 00:10:32,032
把枪扔掉!
Drop the rifle!

147
00:10:32,033 --> 00:10:34,022
快点扔掉
Drop it right now!

148
00:10:34,023 --> 00:10:35,072
退后
Back up.

149
00:10:35,073 --> 00:10:40,092
退后
Back up.

150
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:44,082
你还好吗?
Are you all right?

151
00:10:44,083 --> 00:10:46,071
你们的飞机真的坠毁了?
You really did crash here?

152
00:10:46,072 --> 00:10:49,083
是的 我们还有40多个人
Over 40 of us, yes.

153
00:10:49,084 --> 00:10:53,075
我先进去看看
I'll go in first, make sure it's okay.

154
00:10:53,076 --> 00:10:55,084
你是谁?
Who are you?

155
00:10:55,085 --> 00:10:59,043
我叫Mikhail Bakunin...
My name is Mikhail Bakunin...

156
00:10:59,044 --> 00:11:05,087
我是达摩计划的最后一个存活成员
and I am the last living member of the Dharma Initiative.

157
00:11:11,006 --> 00:11:15,001
小心脚下
Watch your step.

158
00:11:15,002 --> 00:11:21,042
请坐
Please...Sit.

159
00:11:21,043 --> 00:11:25,009
让我来
Here, let me.

160
00:11:25,010 --> 00:11:28,005
你有治疗枪伤的经验?
You've had experience treating gunshot wounds?

161
00:11:28,006 --> 00:11:30,094
我在阿富汗待了一段时间
I spent some time in Afghanistan.

162
00:11:30,095 --> 00:11:33,054
获得了一些战地救助的经验...
I had experience with field medicine...

163
00:11:33,055 --> 00:11:36,053
我在苏联的部队里
in the Soviet army.

164
00:11:36,054 --> 00:11:39,080
厨房里架子上有医疗用品
In the kitchen on the top shelf there is a medical kit.

165
00:11:39,081 --> 00:11:42,083
请你把它拿过来
Will you bring it, please?

166
00:11:42,084 --> 00:11:48,024
没关系的 Kate
It's all right, Kate.

167
00:11:53,060 --> 00:11:55,022
你怎么到这里来的?
How did you get here?

168
00:11:55,023 --> 00:11:57,066
我不知道该从何说起
I almost don't know where to begin.

169
00:11:57,067 --> 00:12:01,005
为什么你不和我说说达摩组织呢?
Why don't you begin with the Dharma Initiative?

170
00:12:01,006 --> 00:12:04,084
我在kiev长大并加入了军队
I grew up in Kiev and joined the Soviet army.

171
00:12:04,085 --> 00:12:10,060
我在vladivostok一个监听站服役
I was stationed at a listening post in Vladivostok.

172
00:12:10,061 --> 00:12:14,099
冷战结束后
After the cold war...

173
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,080
我们冷战输了以后，我们的小队被解散了
After we lost the cold war, my unit was decommissioned.

174
00:12:17,081 --> 00:12:20,079
我离开了军队
I was dismissed from my life in the military,

175
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:26,078
经过了那么多年和敌人的战斗
and after years of conducting unpleasant actions against our enemies

176
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:30,019
我发现我想做些好事
I found myself wanting to do something good

177
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:33,009
后来我被一则报纸上的广告所吸引
so I replied to a newspaper advertisement.

178
00:12:33,010 --> 00:12:34,055
一则广告?
An advertisement?

179
00:12:34,056 --> 00:12:37,083
"你想拯救世界吗?" 它写到
"Would you like toave the world?" It read.

180
00:12:37,084 --> 00:12:40,030
我就是这样知道这个组织的
That's how I met the Initiative.

181
00:12:40,031 --> 00:12:45,084
他们很有钱也很聪明 但必须对外保密
They're very secretive, very rich and very smart.

182
00:12:45,085 --> 00:12:47,095
那么你是什么时候来的?
So when did you come to the island?

183
00:12:47,096 --> 00:12:49,055
11年前
11 years now.

184
00:12:49,056 --> 00:12:53,094
我喜欢电脑 通讯设备
I liked computers, communications equipment

185
00:12:53,095 --> 00:12:57,032
喜欢像灯塔守夜人一样孤独的生活
and being alone like a lighthouse keeper

186
00:12:57,033 --> 00:12:59,055
他们就让我到这个站来了
so they put me in this station.

187
00:12:59,056 --> 00:13:01,070
他们称为"火焰舱"
They called it "The Flame."

188
00:13:01,071 --> 00:13:04,039
火焰舱的用途是什么?
What's the purpose of The Flame?

189
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:10,083
当然是和外界通讯
To communicate with the outside world, of course.

190
00:13:12,070 --> 00:13:17,059
准备好了吗?
Ready to play?

191
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:24,069
准备好了吗?
Ready to play?

192
00:13:31,089 --> 00:13:37,027
到你了
Your move.

193
00:13:38,023 --> 00:13:41,015
达摩组织发生了什么事?
What happened to the Dharma Initiative?

194
00:13:41,016 --> 00:13:43,018
他们全死了
They're all dead, of course.

195
00:13:43,019 --> 00:13:46,085
他们愚蠢的发起了对"敌人"的战争
They foolishly initiated a war against the hostiles

196
00:13:46,086 --> 00:13:50,006
他们叫作"大清洗"
a "purge," they called it.

197
00:13:50,007 --> 00:13:53,074
那你是怎么幸存下来的?
And how did you survive this purge?

198
00:13:53,075 --> 00:13:56,068
我没有参与其中
By not participating in it.

199
00:13:56,069 --> 00:13:57,089
我告诉过你
I told you.

200
00:13:57,090 --> 00:13:59,070
我喜欢独自行动
I like being alone.

201
00:13:59,071 --> 00:14:03,038
那"敌人"们允许你住在这里?
And the hostiles allowed you to stay here?

202
00:14:03,039 --> 00:14:07,039
当一切都结束后 4个人出现在我的田地里
After it was over, four men appeared in the yard.

203
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:09,098
并提出停战协定
They offered a truce.

204
00:14:09,099 --> 00:14:13,061
他们在各个地方划出界限
They said to imagine a line that extended all the way around the valley.

205
00:14:13,062 --> 00:14:19,081
如果我不越线 他们就不会管我
As long as I did not cross it, I would be left alone.

206
00:14:19,082 --> 00:14:23,061
然后他们带走两头牛 我再也没看到过它们
Then they took two cows, and I never saw them again.

207
00:14:23,062 --> 00:14:26,004
他们对那个卫星雷达不感兴趣?
They weren't interested in the satellite dish in the yard?

208
00:14:26,005 --> 00:14:27,050
那又怎么样?
Why would they be?

209
00:14:27,051 --> 00:14:30,049
那个东西几年前就没用了
It hasn't functioned for years.

210
00:14:30,050 --> 00:14:32,078
他们是谁..这些"敌人"?
Who are they..these hostiles?

211
00:14:32,079 --> 00:14:38,080
我不知道 但他们比我们先到这里
I do not know, but they were here for a long time before we were

212
00:14:38,081 --> 00:14:43,092
早很多
A very long time.

213
00:15:05,030 --> 00:15:07,088
我在找Sami
I'm looking for Sami.

214
00:15:07,089 --> 00:15:11,039
Sami!

215
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:15,055
很高兴你能来
I'm so glad you came.

216
00:15:15,056 --> 00:15:16,088
你觉得怎么样?
What do you think?

217
00:15:16,089 --> 00:15:22,031
这是一个简洁的地方 我们有很好的客人
It's a simple place, as you can see, but we have good customers.

218
00:15:22,032 --> 00:15:24,074
这是我的夫人
Here's my wife.

219
00:15:24,075 --> 00:15:28,059
她主管厨房
She's in charge of the kitchen.

220
00:15:28,060 --> 00:15:34,092
Amira 来见Najeev
Amira, come meet Najeev.

221
00:15:39,037 --> 00:15:44,005
很高兴见到你
Pleasure to meet you.

222
00:15:44,006 --> 00:15:46,063
你确定是他么?
Are you sure this is him?

223
00:15:46,064 --> 00:15:49,008
是的
Yes.

224
00:15:49,009 --> 00:15:54,028
你们一定搞错了...
Look, I don't know who you think I am...

225
00:16:24,095 --> 00:16:26,069
你刚才说什么?
What did you just say?

226
00:16:26,070 --> 00:16:29,085
我告诉Nadia礼貌点 因为你们是我的客人
I told Nadia to be polite, because you are my guests.

227
00:16:29,086 --> 00:16:30,047
Nadia?

228
00:16:30,048 --> 00:16:37,057
Nadia Comaneci最出色的体操运动员
After Nadia Comaneci, the greatest athlete the world has ever known.

229
00:16:37,058 --> 00:16:42,092
我们的生日是同一天
We have the same birthday.

230
00:16:47,013 --> 00:16:48,057
现在...
Now...

231
00:16:48,058 --> 00:16:51,050
伤口弄好了
excellent work, if I say myself.

232
00:16:51,051 --> 00:16:53,031
谢谢你 Mikhail
Thank you, Mikhail.

233
00:16:53,032 --> 00:16:57,059
也许我可以为你们弄些冰茶
Perhaps...I can begin to earn your forgiveness by offering some iced tea.

234
00:16:57,060 --> 00:17:03,006
我去看看你们的朋友
I will also check on your friend.

235
00:17:15,065 --> 00:17:17,009
别浪费时间了
Don't waste your time.

236
00:17:17,010 --> 00:17:19,038
十年来我一直想办法打败电脑
For ten years I've tried to defeat that game.

237
00:17:19,039 --> 00:17:22,007
但这个程序是3个博士编写的...
But it was programmed by three grand masters...

238
00:17:22,008 --> 00:17:25,006
而且它还作弊
and it cheats.

239
00:17:25,007 --> 00:17:27,042
我玩过许多电脑
Well I've played a lot of computers

240
00:17:27,043 --> 00:17:30,061
而且很肯定它们不懂怎么作弊
and I'm pretty sure they don't know how to cheat.

241
00:17:30,062 --> 00:17:35,020
这就是为什么我们人类是这么...
That's what makes being human so distinctly...

242
00:17:35,021 --> 00:17:39,080
奇妙
wonderful.

243
00:17:48,003 --> 00:17:49,062
怎么了?
What's wrong?

244
00:17:49,063 --> 00:17:53,028
这...根本没道理
It just...it doesn't make any sense.

245
00:17:53,029 --> 00:17:57,099
他为什么让John和那么多设备器材待在一起?
Why would they let him stay here, with all this stuff, all this equipment?

246
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,016
这再合理不过了
Actually, it makes perfect sense.

247
00:18:00,017 --> 00:18:01,049
你在说什么?
What are you talking about?

248
00:18:01,050 --> 00:18:07,062
他让我们待在这儿 因为他不是达摩的人
The reason they let him stay here is because he is not Dharma.

249
00:18:07,063 --> 00:18:12,036
他是"他们"的人
He is one of them.

250
00:18:14,034 --> 00:18:18,041
他射了你 你还...
He shot you, and you just let him...

251
00:18:18,042 --> 00:18:20,076
我们为什么还待在这儿?
Why are we still sitting here?

252
00:18:20,077 --> 00:18:22,003
我们要待在这里 Kate
We are sitting here, Kate

253
00:18:22,004 --> 00:18:28,004
我确信不止他一个人在这儿
because I am certain he is not alone.

254
00:18:39,014 --> 00:18:44,057
你真的是最棒的吗 大怪脸?
So...you really the number one draft pick, Grimace?

255
00:18:44,058 --> 00:18:48,082
我们用的是"宽容规则"吗?
Are we playing with the mercy rule?

256
00:18:48,083 --> 00:18:50,013
宽容规则?
Mercy rule?

257
00:18:50,014 --> 00:18:56,084
如果我打出11比0 那我就赢了
Yeah,like,If I'm up 11-0, then I, you know, automatically win.

258
00:18:56,085 --> 00:18:58,065
你想赢我11比0?
You're gonna go up 11-0?

259
00:18:58,066 --> 00:19:02,063
不 规则适用双方选手
No, I mean either one of us.

260
00:19:02,064 --> 00:19:03,083
当然
Sure.

261
00:19:03,084 --> 00:19:06,063
我们可以用这个规则
We can have a mercy rule.

262
00:19:06,064 --> 00:19:08,007
我能发球吗?
Do you wanna volley for serve?

263
00:19:08,008 --> 00:19:11,059
随便你
I'll tell you what...Be my guest.

264
00:19:11,060 --> 00:19:15,013
干掉他 Hurley
Take him down, Hurley.

265
00:19:15,014 --> 00:19:17,029
加油 Hurley

266
