0比0
0 serving 0.

267
00:19:28,024 --> 00:19:33,012
1比0
1-Nothing.

268
00:19:37,044 --> 00:19:41,071
我自己做的茶 如果有点苦的话请别介意
I grow the tea myself, so pardon its bitterness.

269
00:19:41,072 --> 00:19:43,018
我们十分感激
Any tea is good tea.

270
00:19:43,019 --> 00:19:47,053
我们很长时间没见过冰了
You know how long it's been since we've seen ice?

271
00:19:47,054 --> 00:19:51,070
我发现站周围有许多粗电线
I noticed a series of thick wires as I walked around the station.

272
00:19:51,071 --> 00:19:53,085
这是网络集线器
This is the hub,

273
00:19:53,086 --> 00:19:56,019
和这岛上的其它站相连接
but they go underground to various stations all over the island.

274
00:19:56,020 --> 00:19:58,078
有没有一根是通向大海的?
And these cables--do any of them run into the ocean?

275
00:19:58,079 --> 00:20:02,069
是的 海底电缆连接的声纳
Yes. There is an underwater beacon that emits sonar pings

276
00:20:02,070 --> 00:20:04,035
为船只导航
to help guide in the vessels.

277
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:06,004
导航 你是说潜水艇吗?
By vessels, you mean submarines?

278
00:20:06,005 --> 00:20:07,078
是的
Yes.

279
00:20:07,079 --> 00:20:10,060
并且它有自主判断能力
The Initiative used one to bring us here

280
00:20:10,061 --> 00:20:12,092
但现在它不是被"敌人"销毁
but I can imagine only that the hostiles have either destroyed

281
00:20:12,093 --> 00:20:15,055
就是被他们操控了
or commandeered it by now.

282
00:20:15,056 --> 00:20:16,094
这就能解释他们
That explains how they were able

283
00:20:16,095 --> 00:20:20,000
饶开我的位点 并夺走了我们的帆船
to get round my position and capture our sailboat.

284
00:20:20,001 --> 00:20:22,083
你们有帆船?
You have a sailboat?

285
00:20:22,084 --> 00:20:26,049
直到被"敌人"抢走
Till we lost it to your hostiles.

286
00:20:26,050 --> 00:20:31,050
那太不幸了
That's very unfortunate.

287
00:20:31,086 --> 00:20:38,009
至少我们能杀了其中的一个人
Well...at least we were able to kill one them.

288
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:47,020
我们为什么还要兜圈子呢...
Why are we continuing to play this little game...

289
00:20:47,021 --> 00:20:53,051
为什么不直接切入正题?
when we all know it has moved to the next stage?

290
00:21:20,011 --> 00:21:24,099
拿些绳子来
Get some rope.

291
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:49,012
喝了它
Drink.

292
00:21:59,055 --> 00:22:05,091
你在共和国卫队里是个拷问官吧?
You were a torturer, were you not, in the Republican Guard?

293
00:22:05,092 --> 00:22:10,064
难道你认不出你的受害者了?
Do you not recognize one of your victims?

294
00:22:10,065 --> 00:22:14,020
难道你不记得被你折磨的女人了吗?
Do you not recognize the woman that you tortured?

295
00:22:14,021 --> 00:22:16,032
难道你认不出我妻子了吗?!
Do you not recognize my wife?!

296
00:22:16,033 --> 00:22:20,091
不 我...
No, I've never...

297
00:22:20,092 --> 00:22:26,097
你一定是搞错了
You've confused me with someone else.

298
00:22:29,020 --> 00:22:35,019
Amira因为窝藏敌人的罪名被捕了
Amira was arrested for harboring an enemy of the state.

299
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:43,039
在她被关押的3个月间 她被拷问无数次
She was held for three months while she was questioned.

300
00:22:43,054 --> 00:22:48,033
她的手臂上满是伤疤
Her arms bear the scars of those questions.

301
00:22:48,034 --> 00:22:56,020
我向你保证 Najeev 我没有弄错
So I assure you, Najeev, I am not confused.

302
00:22:57,021 --> 00:23:00,048
我的名字不是Najeev
My name is not Najeev.

303
00:23:00,049 --> 00:23:03,064
我叫Sayid Jarrah
I am Sayid Jarrah.

304
00:23:03,065 --> 00:23:06,030
我曾在共和国卫队
I was in the Republican Guard

305
00:23:06,031 --> 00:23:09,085
而且我是个拷问官 但我从来没见过你的妻子
and, yes, I was an interrogator, but I have never seen your wife.

306
00:23:09,086 --> 00:23:11,059
也许她在哪里见过我
Maybe she saw me at the same facility

307
00:23:11,060 --> 00:23:14,072
但我的确不认识她!
but I do not know her!

308
00:23:14,073 --> 00:23:18,081
我记得每一个我拷问的人
I can remember every face of every person I've interrogated.

309
00:23:18,082 --> 00:23:24,024
她记得你的脸
She remembers your face.

310
00:23:24,025 --> 00:23:28,047
她一踏进你们的饭店
She remembers it so well that she recognized it from a mere glimpse

311
00:23:28,048 --> 00:23:36,090
就认出你来了!
when we walked by the restaurant where you worked!

312
00:23:44,038 --> 00:23:46,061
你要我做什么?
What do you want from me?

313
00:23:46,062 --> 00:23:53,059
我要你承认你所做的 否则
I want you to admit to what you did, And if you don't

314
00:23:53,060 --> 00:23:59,032
你想要离开这里 只有被装进那包里了
you will leave this room in that bag.

315
00:24:07,026 --> 00:24:09,025
你怎么知道他不是一个人?
How do you know he isn't alone?

316
00:24:09,026 --> 00:24:11,043
外面的那匹马还装有马鞍
The horse outside is still saddled

317
00:24:11,044 --> 00:24:14,087
而且马镫的设置比这个男人的脚要短许多
And the stirrups are set up for someone much shorter than this man.

318
00:24:14,088 --> 00:24:18,009
你认为"The others"派人来让他合作?
You think the others sent someone to keep him company?

319
00:24:18,010 --> 00:24:21,093
他们派人来是因为他们失去了联系
They sent someone out here because they lost communications.

320
00:24:21,094 --> 00:24:24,032
也许是因为天空变成了紫色?
Maybe when the sky turned purple?

321
00:24:24,033 --> 00:24:26,014
这正是我所想的
That would be my guess.

322
00:24:26,015 --> 00:24:28,044
如果有人在这里的话 他一定藏的很好
If there's someone else here, they're hiding pretty good.

323
00:24:28,045 --> 00:24:34,095
我检查过这地方的每个角落...
I checked every nook and cranny of this place...

324
00:24:35,086 --> 00:24:41,038
还不够彻底
Not every nook and cranny.

325
00:25:08,066 --> 00:25:11,004
你准备好说实话了吗?
Are you ready to tell me the truth?

326
00:25:11,005 --> 00:25:16,062
我已经把实话告诉你了
I have told you the truth.

327
00:25:17,055 --> 00:25:20,046
我不认识你
I do not know you

328
00:25:20,047 --> 00:25:24,046
你折磨过她!
You tortured her.

329
00:25:24,047 --> 00:25:25,065
不
No.

330
00:25:25,066 --> 00:25:31,034
我从不碰女人
I would never touch a woman

331
00:25:34,065 --> 00:25:37,015
你认为这样做
Do you think this will do any good

332
00:25:37,016 --> 00:25:40,064
会让我承认我没做过的事?
that this will make me confess to something I didn't do?

333
00:25:40,065 --> 00:25:43,072
我妻子说了实话
My wife confessed to something she didn't do.

334
00:25:43,073 --> 00:25:47,078
而你却用烧开的油烫她的手臂
She confessed when you poured a pan of boiling oil over her arms.

335
00:25:47,079 --> 00:25:49,044
不 你一定弄错了...
No, I did not. You have the wrong...

336
00:25:49,045 --> 00:25:54,032
承认吧!
Admit it!

337
00:25:54,033 --> 00:26:00,062
我不能承认我没做过的事
I cannot admit to something I didn't do.

338
00:26:07,056 --> 00:26:12,067
今天到此为止吧
That is enough for today.

339
00:26:17,039 --> 00:26:22,070
我明天还会再来
Then I will see you tomorrow.

340
00:26:53,030 --> 00:26:58,008
到你了
Your move.

341
